@NODE "HistoryI"
@TITLE "Release V0.9"
@NEXT "HistoryJ"
@PREV "HistoryH"
@TOC "HistoryLog"
@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}- Laplace Manual ---------------------------------------------- Release V0.9 -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}

@REM KEY 0 0 "HistoryLog" "Release V0.9"
@{B}Release V0.9@{UB} (beta-release) released 9.1.1998

--------------------------- NOW IT'S SHAREWARE!!!  ---------------------------
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}7.5.1997@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 4 @{UI}:  Now uses  CGFonts for  displaying. Terribly  slow, have to
      rewrite the routines..
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 7 @{UI}: wow, really nice looking brackets ;-)
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}21.6.1997@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 17 @{UI}: finally kicked out  this fuckin' Texinfo! now I'm using  my
      own textprocessing-system  `TeXas'.  boring  slow  but  incredibly
      flexible!
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}7.9.1997@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 25 @{UI}: One of the biggest problems that you encounter, if you are
      a coder, is that you are constantly learning new programing  tech-
      niques. Because if you do so, you don't want to use the old way. I
      just started coding in  C++ (after buying 16MB,  so I can use  the
      GCC compiler). This means that it's absolutely impossible for  me,
      to continue writing in  ANSI-C. The only  possible solution is  to
      rewrite Laplace completely in C++... This may take some time...
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}8.9.1997@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 26 @{UI}: Can you imagine this: this stupid guy wants to rewrite the
      whole code of Laplace in C++!!  55000 lines!! I wonder what  would
      happen, if he could direct this work on his physic studies...
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}9.1.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 27 @{UI}:  Oh shit...  Three fuckin' month  are gone...  But here  it
      is... V0.9, ready for release!!!!
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}11.1.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 28 @{UI}:  german error  messages weren't  up-to-date. Removed files
      'Data/Catalogs/deutsch/#?'. Now uses english messages by default.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 29 @{UI}: rewrote startup window code. Now it's loaded as an external
      module.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 30  @{UI}: preferences  now support  presets.  german menus  are now
      available


@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}------------------------------------------------------------------ ® by P!\K -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}
@ENDNODE
@NODE "HistoryJ"
@TITLE "Release V0.10"
@NEXT "HistoryK"
@PREV "HistoryI"
@TOC "HistoryLog"
@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}- Laplace Manual --------------------------------------------- Release V0.10 -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}

@REM KEY 0 0 "HistoryLog" "Release V0.10"
@{B}Release V0.10@{UB} (beta-release) released 29.1.1998

 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}14.1.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 1 @{UI}: Changed @{I}array() @{UI} to @{I}newarray() @{UI}. I need @{B}array@{UB} for something
      else.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 2 @{UI}: New function @{I}genarray() @{UI}.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 3 @{UI}: Invented new type system. Changes syntax of procedure decla-
      ration, e.g. @{I}number p(vector x) { x * x; } @{UI}.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}15.1.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 4 @{UI}: There was an endless loop, when simplifying @{I}1/sqrt(x) @{UI}.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 5 @{UI}: Startup window now uses AHI for sound replay.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 6 @{UI}: A plotter is coming... I can see him at the horizon!
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}16.1.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 7 @{UI}: After a  long, long night (I could  say 'good morning' to  a
      flatmate...), a basic function plotter is working.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}22.1.1998@{UB}
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 8  @{UI}: Startupwindow:  AHI kicked  out again,  now uses  datatypes
      (which might use AHI, if installed...)
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 9 @{UI}:  Animated plots!!! Wasn't  very difficult,  a first version
      worked after 20mins o' codin'...
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}23.1.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 10 @{UI}: You may even show multiple plot anims... >KILL YOUR PROCES-
      SOR!!!!<
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}28.1.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 11 @{UI}: Well, the plotter seems to work so far, time for a new re-
      lease...


@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}------------------------------------------------------------------ ® by P!\K -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}
@ENDNODE
@NODE "HistoryK"
@TITLE "Release V0.11"
@NEXT "HistoryL"
@PREV "HistoryJ"
@TOC "HistoryLog"
@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}- Laplace Manual --------------------------------------------- Release V0.11 -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}

@REM KEY 0 0 "HistoryLog" "Release V0.11"
@{B}Release V0.11@{UB}  (beta-release) released 27.2.1998

 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}29.1.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 2 @{UI}: You can use @{I}array(...) @{UI} for creating arrays again.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}30.1.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 3 @{UI}:  You can now  edit some global  plotter settings. These  are
      used, when a new plotter is opened. If you modify some local plot-
      ter settings, the global settings are updated, too. So you  always
      get the settings of the last plotter, if you open a new one.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}2.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 4 @{UI}: Restructured internal  plotter handling, making further  ex-
      tensions easier.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 5 @{UI}: Reimplemented image caching for faster display update. Still
      to be improved.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 6  @{UI}: Added  @{B}prompt@{UB}, @{B}seperator  thickness@{UB} and  @{B}center results@{UB}  to
      preferences. These were options before, what didn't make sense...
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}3.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 7 @{UI}: Plotter settings for  functions (color, precision etc.) are
      now saved, too.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 8 @{UI}: You can now remove functions from a plotter in the settings
      window.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 9 @{UI}: Added  the ability to plot  functions @{I}[x(t),y(t)], t=a...b @{UI}
      instead of normal functions ...[x,y(x)], x=a...b
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 10 @{UI}: Cool!! Animated Lissajous-figures.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}4.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 11 @{UI}: Changed syntax of some functions, now using intervals:
      @{B}@{BG FILL}@{FG FILLTEXT}>@{UB}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT} genarray(a=1 .. 2, f(a))
      @{B}@{BG FILL}@{FG FILLTEXT}>@{UB}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT} genvector(a=1 .. 2, f(a))
      @{B}@{BG FILL}@{FG FILLTEXT}>@{UB}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT} genmatrix(a=1 .. 2, b=1 .. 2, f(a,b))
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 12 @{UI}: Function graph thickness  implemented. Currently only 1, 2
      or 3.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 13  @{UI}: New  class @{B}integral@{UB}.  Currently  there are  no operations
      available for it, but numerical integration is comming up next.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 14 @{UI}: Repaired my shoes... no money for new ones.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 15  @{UI}: And  here it  is... Numerical  integration. Try  something
      like:
      @{B}@{BG FILL}@{FG FILLTEXT}>@{UB}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT} A = integral( x^2, x=0..1 )
      @{B}@{BG FILL}@{FG FILLTEXT}>@{UB}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT} nint(A)
         Adjust precision with @{B}$intprec@{UB}, the higher the better.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}5.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 16 @{UI}: Now you can use intervals in indeces: @{I}A[2 .. 3, 2 .. 3] @{UI} ->
      fetch a 2x2 matrix from the bigger matrix @{I}A @{UI}
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}6.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 17 @{UI}: Now generates an error message, if you use arguments for a
      reference, which is itself an argument,  e.g. @{I}f(x) = x(2) @{UI}. Thanx
      to Myk Hoole for is bug report.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 18 @{UI}: Cursor is now blinking again...
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 19 @{UI}: Fonts and colors  are now updated correctly, when  modified
      in the preferences.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 20 @{UI}: Display  for greek letters in  the preferences window used
      wrong font.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}16.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 21 @{UI}: As reported, the  startup window still causes problems.  If
      nothing helps, it can be turned off completly.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 22 @{UI}: Fixed  a bug when displaying  things like @{I}x ^  1 / a @{UI}.  Re-
      ported by Rolf Kabbe.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 23  @{UI}: Fixed  a bug  of the  vector product.  Reported by  Sascha
      Werth.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 24 @{UI}: It is now possible to export a project as ASCII even with-
      out a keyfile. The import function is disabled instead.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}17.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 25 @{UI}: You can set the x-range directly with with @{I}plot() @{UI} command:
      @{I}plot(f(x), x=a..b) @{UI}
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}18.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 26 @{UI}: @{I}derive(x ^ x, x) @{UI}  was wrong. Not the bug reported by Rolf
      Kabbe, but is report was a hint...
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 27 @{UI}: Simplification of  @{I}x ^ a+1 @{UI} caused  an endless loop. @{I}This @{UI}
      was the bug reported by Rolf Kabbe.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}21.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 28 @{UI}: Improved syntax of @{I}animate() @{UI}, e.g.
      @{B}@{BG FILL}@{FG FILLTEXT}>@{UB}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT} animate(f(x,t), x=-1..1, t=0..10)
         Intervals are optional.
    @{B}À@{UB} @{I}▀ 29 @{UI}: Fixed and improved image caching (for buttons and  Pierre's
      face).


@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}------------------------------------------------------------------ ® by P!\K -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}
@ENDNODE
@NODE "HistoryL"
@TITLE "Release V0.12"
@NEXT "HistoryM"
@PREV "HistoryK"
@TOC "HistoryLog"
@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}- Laplace Manual --------------------------------------------- Release V0.12 -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}

@REM KEY 0 0 "HistoryLog" "Release V0.12"
@{B}Release V0.12@{UB}  (beta-release) released 7.4.1998

 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}28.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀1: Rearranged internal number handling. Error distribution should
      work now for complex numbers,  too. Plotter and integrals can  now
      contain complex  operations,  as long  as  the result  is  a  real
      number.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}1.3.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀2: Entries can  now directly be  marked. Click on  the left  most
      part of the text area (the space inhabited by the prompt) to  tog-
      gle, or use the menu.
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀3: Export entries as LaTeX.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}2.3.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀4: New operators @{I}ceil() @{UI} and @{I}floor() @{UI}.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}5.3.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀5: Added registration and bug report forms.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}6.3.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀6: Added undo/redo facility. Press HELP for undo, SHIFT-HELP  for
      redo.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}14.3.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀7: New sections @{"Environment variables" LINK "GettingStarted.guide/Environment"} and @{"Command line options" LINK "GettingStarted.guide/CmdOptions"}.
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀8: New section @{"Reporting bugs" LINK "Introduction.guide/BugReports"}.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}16.3.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀9: You can now @{I}cut @{UI}, @{I}copy @{UI} and @{I}paste @{UI} marked entries.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}18.3.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀10: Added implicit multiplication,  e.g. @{I}2 a @{UI}  -> @{I}2*a @{UI}. But  it's
      not possible after references, because things like @{I}a b @{UI} are always
      treated as @{I}a(b) @{UI} (function @{I}a @{UI} with argument @{I}b @{UI}).
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}31.3.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀11: Small bugfixes, found in symbolic derivation.


@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}------------------------------------------------------------------ ® by P!\K -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}
@ENDNODE
@NODE "HistoryM"
@TITLE "Release V0.13"
@PREV "HistoryL"
@TOC "HistoryLog"
@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}- Laplace Manual --------------------------------------------- Release V0.13 -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}

@REM KEY 0 0 "HistoryLog" "Release V0.13"
@{B}Release V0.13@{UB}  (beta-release) released 30.9.1998

 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}8.4.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀1: Bugfix: redrawing wath screwed up with asynchron calculation.
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀2: Plotter: First simple PS export.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}12.4.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀3: Plotter: PS and EPS export works fine.
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀4: Plotter: Added axis labels and legend.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}13.4.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀5: Plotter: Now displays e.g @{I}2*10 ^ 2 @{UI} instead of @{I}2e2 @{UI}.
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀6: Manual: New appendix @{"Future plans" LINK "Future"}.
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀7: Plotter: Axis number were place incorrectly with log scale.
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀8: Plotter: GhostScript  (if installed) can  now directly be  in-
      voked to print PS files.
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀9: : Plotter: Preview using GhostScript implemented.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}16.4.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀10: : Plotter: New (adaptive) handling of function's precision.
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀11: : Plotter: More flexible handling of axises.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}17.4.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀12: : Bugfix: Expressions like @{I}1  + 2x @{UI} caused a crash.  Reported
      by ??.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}18.4.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀13: New internal representation  of displayed objects. Uses  less
      code and prepares Laplace for a possible PPC port.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}19.4.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀14: Plotter:  You can  abort  a zoom  operation by  pressing  the
      spacebar while the left mouse button is pressed.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}20.4.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀15: Plotter: Fixed some problems with logarithmic scale.
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀16:  Plotter:  The  window  is   not  activated,  if  opened   by
      @{I}plot_open() @{UI}. Suggested by Christoph Rickers.
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀17: Button images are now  loaded before the window contents  are
      drawn. Looks more professional according to Christoph Rickers...
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}29.4.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀18: Plotter: you can now change the fonts.
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀19: Prefs: Use listview instead of register.
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀20: About: New page @{B}Modules@{UB}.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}9.5.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀21: Some modifications of the GUI (image buttons, etc.).
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀22: Reimplemented online help system.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}11.5.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀23: Uff, what a day. Once again, my @{"address" LINK "Introduction.guide/Address"} has changed! Now it's
         Scheffelstra▀e 14
         69214 Eppelheim
         Germany
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀24: Bugfix: Derivation of @{I}a ^ c, c=@{UI}const@{I} @{UI} was wrong (@{I}c*a ^ (c-1) @{UI}
      instead of @{I}c*a  ^ (c-1)*derive  (a,x) @{UI}). Reported  by Markus  Man-
      nevaara.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}16.5.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀25: After logically splitting Laplace into the mathmatical kernel
      and the graphical  interface, these two  parts are now  physically
      seperated into two programs that communicate via messages. In the-
      ory the kernal can now be compiled for and run on a PPC while  the
      GUI uses the 68k processor. If you  have a PPC card, you are  pro-
      gramming with the ppc-gcc and you would like to port the kernel to
      PPC, please contact me!
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}14.7.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀26: Bugfix: derivation of constants (pi, e) caused Enforcer  hit.
      Reported by Tommy Lindgren.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}15.7.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀27: Implemented @{I}Line archive @{UI} and @{I}Color archive @{UI} for easier  line
      and color definition.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}30.7.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}À@{UB} ▀28: Bugfix: custom MUI classes where disposed before all MUI  ob-
      jects where disposed, which could  sometimes lead into a crash  at
      the exit of Laplace.
 @{B}À@{UB} @{B}29.9.1998@{UB}:
         Finally it's out.


